From 1ac04852463ba32e0fd8ea6bdca3c143783449de Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Stephen Lang <skl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 01:57:07 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] feat(spec): generate conformance corpus from the jest
 suite

Run the real, unmodified jest spec files with the public API wrapped in
recording proxies, and write every promql.* call and Expression usage the
suite makes to spec/fixtures/conformance.json as language-agnostic cases
of the form { fn, params, expected | error }.

This corpus is the behavioural contract for non-TypeScript implementations
of the tsqtsq API: TypeScript stays the source of truth, developed and
tested idiomatically with jest, and other implementations replay the
recorded corpus to prove equivalence.

Regenerate with: pnpm run generate:fixtures (deterministic output).
prettify is excluded: it wraps the lezer PromQL parser and is
TypeScript-only by design.
